projectInfo.name: GeoNightMapathon2021
projectInfo.shortDescription:
Public Lab Mongolia (PLM), a local non-governmental organization in Mongolia, is leading the Mongolian chapter for volunteer mappers through the HOT OSM's Missing Maps project, as part of their mission to promote open data and disaster preparedness.
The international "Night of Geography", promoted by EUGEO and IGU, will be held on 9 April 2021.The GeoNight is an initiative proposed for the first time by the CNFG (French National Geographical Committee) at a National scale in 2017. From 2018 onwards, the initiative has expanded internationally, first in Europe,
projectInfo.description:
Public Lab Mongolia (PLM), a local non-governmental organization in Mongolia, is leading the Mongolian chapter for volunteer mappers through the HOT OSM's Missing Maps project, as part of their mission to promote open data and disaster preparedness.

This project is to map the two khoroo/ward of Songinokhairkhan district in Ulaanbaatar city, Mongolia, is organized by PLM in collaboration with the HOT Community Mappers Mongolia Program participants and the volunteer mappers will be instrumental in creating an integrated geographic database of all aimag/province centers. Up-to-date, quality data means better decision-making in case of emergencies and disasters.
projectInfo.instructions:
Roads appear as lines lighter than the background soil/grass. Roads can be paved or dirt. Paved roads have mostly been mapped/marked. Please focus on mapping dirt roads (which tend to spiral more)

Fences may or may not be very visible. Fences are structures often used to mark land ownership boundaries of residential houses, office,s and more.

Buildings appear mostly rectangular shapes. A building can be offices and residential houses.

Gers appear as white circular shapes. This is the Mongolian traditional house.
